{"parentUuid":"eed22599-475a-40b1-81bf-ad02abd30a6c","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"74ab6cc1-259e-4f35-896b-31737bc09d28","agentId":"a8eae6b52af6c3ba8","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012QYmi8Xc6gTwDPkESWgKmb","type":"tool_result","content":"7:%   - base Mistral-v0.1 core7 hardening batch (P0, head sweep, SVD, path patching, mediation, dual patch, mode atlas)\n14:%   (1) R_V is geometric SIGNATURE/readout, not causal mechanism\n15:%   (2) Signed Cohen's d throughout — no |d| notation\n74:Base-model path patching localizes the strongest causal site to the early residual stream\n93:For AI safety, $\\RV < 0.737$ detects self-referential content with AUROC~$= 0.909$,\n122:Our strongest current base-v0.1 evidence is causal and mechanistic.\n146:absent in other high-complexity modes and causally necessary (Section~\\ref{sec:causal}).\n153:Path patching (Section~\\ref{sec:causal}) shows that V-projection activations---where\n154:$\\RV$ is measured---do not define the primary causal bottleneck.\n158:$\\RV$ is a geometric \\emph{readout} of upstream processing, not the causal mechanism itself.\n164:Two claims survive the causal analysis.\n175:(1)~We define $\\RV$ and characterize its detection properties (AUROC~$= 0.909$;\n179:(3)~Path patching localizes the causal site to the early residual stream ($\\dcohen = 4.14$ at L5),\n180:establishing $\\RV$ as a downstream readout (Section~\\ref{sec:causal}).\n255:$\\RV < 0.737$              & Self-referential & TPR~$= 0.833$; FPR~$= 0.139$; AUROC~$= 0.909$ \\\\\n405:\\caption{\\textbf{Cross-architecture effect sizes.}\n406:         Signed Cohen's $\\dcohen$: negative = contraction, positive = expansion.\n434:\\caption{\\textbf{Cross-architecture effect sizes.}\n477:\\label{sec:causal}\n479:We perform three causal interventions to determine the relationship between\n482:% BASE: path patching numbers from\n514:inconsistent with a simple late-layer V-projection causal story.\n516:$\\RV$ as a geometric \\emph{readout} of upstream computation rather than the causal node itself.\n668:($n_\\text{self} = 50$, $n_\\text{other} = 450$), we achieve AUROC~$= 0.909$.\n699:         (a) AUROC~$= 0.909$ for self-referential content detection.\n727:\\citep{heimersheim2024activation} enable causal localization.\n791:processing that is \\emph{detectable} (AUROC $= 0.909$),\n793:and \\emph{mechanistically informative}: the strongest available base-model causal leverage sits in\n800:causally generated (early residual stream) is relevant beyond this study: many geometric\n842:All effect sizes are computed with bootstrap BCa 95\\% CIs (5{,}000 resamples).\n867:\\caption{Selected effect sizes with current provenance status.}\n901:$^{h}$Cohen's $h$ (proportion effect size); all other rows use Cohen's $d$.\n910:The refreshed base 32-layer $\\times$ 3-component path patching map reveals a layered causal\n914:Layers 0--5 show the strongest causal effect, peaking at L5\n915:($\\dcohen = 4.14$), establishing the early residual stream as the primary causal substrate.","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"c104ebdb-7741-4529-bbfa-2fc45d39ed47","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:46:38.485Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"eed22599-475a-40b1-81bf-ad02abd30a6c","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
