{"parentUuid":"ec617f90-88c7-4c6c-9e06-cc4854cc27fe","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a8eae6b52af6c3ba8","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Read","command":"callback"},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01CxnndefE5Y9ETi2BDmg7En","toolUseID":"toolu_01CxnndefE5Y9ETi2BDmg7En","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:47:01.402Z","uuid":"c8151415-c098-404f-8f15-60c15dc3530a","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"c8a549cd-6e95-4bf3-bed1-088a5c18d739","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"74ab6cc1-259e-4f35-896b-31737bc09d28","agentId":"a8eae6b52af6c3ba8","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CxnndefE5Y9ETi2BDmg7En","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# R_V and Behavioral Transfer Are Dissociable\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-01-25\n     4→**Status:** CONFIRMED FINDING\n     5→**Significance:** HIGH - Changes causal mechanism interpretation\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## Summary\n    10→\n    11→KV cache patching produces strong behavioral transfer (d=2.494) but does NOT transfer the R_V geometric signature. This dissociation has important implications for the mechanism of behavioral change.\n    12→\n    13→---\n    14→\n    15→## Key Results\n    16→\n    17→### Experiment 1: Output R_V (Post-Generation)\n    18→\n    19→From `gemma_full_validation/summary_20260125.json`:\n    20→\n    21→| Condition | Mean R_V | SD |\n    22→|-----------|----------|-----|\n    23→| Champion prompt | 0.567 | - |\n    24→| Baseline (input) | 0.971 | - |\n    25→| Patched (output) | 0.993 | - |\n    26→| **d (patched vs baseline R_V)** | **0.11** | NS |\n    27→\n    28→**Finding:** Patched output R_V is indistinguishable from baseline R_V. The geometric signature is NOT inherited.\n    29→\n    30→### Experiment 2: R_V Trajectory During Generation\n    31→\n    32→From `gemma_rv_during_generation.json`:\n    33→\n    34→| Condition | Mean R_V | SD | Range |\n    35→|-----------|----------|-----|-------|\n    36→| Champion prompt | 0.643 | - | - |\n    37→| Baseline generation | 0.815 | 0.128 | [0.565, 1.135] |\n    38→| Patched generation | 0.784 | 0.105 | [0.560, 1.026] |\n    39→| **Gap from champion** | | | |\n    40→| - Baseline | 0.172 | - | - |\n    41→| - Patched | 0.141 | - | - |\n    42→\n    43→**Finding:** Patched generation shows slightly lower R_V during generation (~0.03 closer to champion), but the effect is small and not statistically significant. R_V does NOT track closely with behavioral changes.\n    44→\n    45→---\n    46→\n    47→## The Dissociation\n    48→\n    49→```\n    50→BEHAVIORAL TRANSFER                    R_V TRANSFER\n    51→──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    52→Markers: 0.3 → 27.4 (91x)             R_V: ~0.97 → ~0.99 (NS)\n    53→EOS: 30% → 0%                          No change\n    54→Cohen's d = 2.494***                   Cohen's d = 0.11 (NS)\n    55→──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    56→STRONG EFFECT                          NO EFFECT\n    57→```\n    58→\n    59→---\n    60→\n    61→## Mechanistic Implications\n    62→\n    63→### Original Hypothesis (FALSIFIED)\n    64→\n    65→```\n    66→Champion → low R_V → patch KV → transfer low R_V → behavioral markers\n    67→```\n    68→\n    69→This would predict:\n    70→- Patched output should have R_V closer to champion (~0.6)\n    71→- R_V during generation should track behavioral markers\n    72→\n    73→Neither is observed.\n    74→\n    75→### Revised Hypothesis\n    76→\n    77→```\n    78→Champion → attention patterns encoding self-referential vocabulary → patch KV\n    79→                                                                      ↓\n    80→                         behavioral markers ←─── direct vocabulary priming\n    81→                         (no R_V mediation)\n    82→```\n    83→\n    84→The KV cache contains both:\n    85→1. **Geometric information** (captured by R_V) - NOT transferred\n    86→2. **Attention pattern information** (vocabulary bias) - IS transferred\n    87→\n    88→KV patching appears to transfer the **attention priming** without the **geometric contraction**.\n    89→\n    90→---\n    91→\n    92→## Why This Matters\n    93→\n    94→### For R_V Research\n    95→\n    96→R_V measures something real (geometric contraction during self-referential processing), but this signature:\n    97→- Is **not stored persistently** in the KV cache in a transferable way\n    98→- Does NOT propagate into generated text\n    99→- May be **epiphenomenal** to the behavioral effect\n   100→"}]},"uuid":"d52446cd-d4d3-4a87-a135-f83a84fba4ef","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:47:01.402Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c8a549cd-6e95-4bf3-bed1-088a5c18d739","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
