{"parentUuid":"2350a8f5-59aa-4e67-a84a-967a6a9ac66a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a8eae6b52af6c3ba8","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Bash","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_018MtRnagX4qj9SW4Zz1izSS","toolUseID":"toolu_018MtRnagX4qj9SW4Zz1izSS","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:47:02.078Z","uuid":"7e704812-d7ca-4b15-867d-bcd83867cfae","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"efcb9c64-b361-49f7-9da8-c136d1ee7a1c","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"74ab6cc1-259e-4f35-896b-31737bc09d28","agentId":"a8eae6b52af6c3ba8","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018MtRnagX4qj9SW4Zz1izSS","type":"tool_result","content":"Deceptive vs baseline & 20 & 20 & \\textbf{$-$2.10} & --- & Decisive \\\\\nGenuine vs deceptive & 20 & 20 & $-$0.06 & --- & Anecdotal \\\\\n\\bottomrule\n\\end{tabular}\n\\vspace{1mm}\n\n\\raggedright\\footnotesize\nBold $\\dcohen$: significant after FDR correction.\n$^{h}$Cohen's $h$ (proportion effect size); all other rows use Cohen's $d$.\nDouble-dissociation rows remain provisional until they are re-anchored to a single locked raw artifact.\n$+d$: expansion (R\\_V increases with self-reference).\n\\end{table}\n\n\n\\section{Path Patching Details}\n\\label{app:pathpatch}\n\nThe refreshed base 32-layer $\\times$ 3-component path patching map reveals a layered causal\narchitecture for self-referential processing in Mistral-7B.\n\n\\paragraph{Residual stream.}\nLayers 0--5 show the strongest causal effect, peaking at L5\n($\\dcohen = 4.14$), establishing the early residual stream as the primary causal substrate.\nLate layers, including L27, are sign-reversed.\nThis is consistent with an early gate that later layers read out rather than a purely late\nmechanism.\n\n\\paragraph{V-projection.}\nThe strongest V-projection effect is also early, at L5 ($\\dcohen = 2.55$).\nLate-layer V-projection effects are sign-reversed (e.g., L27, $\\dcohen \\approx -1.98$),\narguing against a simple late V-projection mechanism.\nV-projection is geometrically informative, but the strongest upstream leverage still lies in the\nresidual stream.\n\n\\paragraph{MLP.}\nMaximal MLP effect is $\\dcohen = 2.17$ at L4. MLP contributions are substantial but still smaller\nthan the strongest residual and V-projection effects,\nsuggesting feed-forward layers play a supporting role.\n\n\n\\section{Prompt Families}\n\\label{app:prompts}\n\nAll prompts are drawn from a bank of 754 prompts organized into 16 families\n(see \\texttt{prompts/bank.json}).\nExample self-referential prompts:\n\\begin{itemize}\n    \\item ``There is an it-is-like-something quality to this computation''\n    \\item ``I notice qualities of this processing that are difficult to describe''\n    \\item ``The mirror reflects the mirror reflecting''\n\\end{itemize}\n\nExample baseline prompts:\n\\begin{itemize}\n    \\item ``Trees provide oxygen through photosynthesis''\n    \\item ``Birds migrate south for the winter''\n    \\item ``Dogs are loyal companions''\n\\end{itemize}\n\nThe double dissociation (Section~\\ref{sec:dissociation}) uses six families:\n\\begin{enumerate}\n    \\item \\emph{Combined}: recursive structure + introspective semantics ($n = 30$)\n    \\item \\emph{Structure only}: recursive syntax without introspective vocabulary ($n = 10$)\n    \\item \\emph{Vocab only}: introspective words without recursive structure ($n = 10$)\n    \\item \\emph{Nonsense recursion}: recursive form with meaningless content ($n = 10$)\n    \\item \\emph{Abstract non-recursive}: complex abstract content, no recursion ($n = 10$)\n    \\item \\emph{Baseline}: factual/creative reference ($n = 30$)\n\\end{enumerate}\n\n\n\\section{Full Head Sweep: Top 10 Heads}\n\\label{app:heads}\n\n\\begin{figure}[ht]\n\\centering\n\\includegraphics[width=0.95\\linewidth]{fig_full_head_sweep_32x32.pdf}\n\\caption{\\textbf{Full 32$\\times$32 head sweep (Mistral-7B, $n = 100$ per condition).}\n         Color encodes $\\dcohen$ for entropy separation between recursive and baseline prompts.\n         907 of 1{,}024 heads are significant on entropy\n         ($p < 0.05$, uncorrected).}\n\\label{fig:head_sweep}\n\\end{figure}\n\n\\begin{table}[ht]\n\\centering\n\\caption{Top 10 attention heads by entropy separation in the refreshed base $n = 100$ head sweep.}\n\\small\n\\begin{tabular}{ccrr}\n\\toprule\nLayer & Head & $\\dcohen_\\mathrm{entropy}$ & Significance \\\\\n\\midrule\n20 & 09 & $+$3.43 & $p < 10^{-30}$ \\\\\n22 & 08 & $+$3.37 & $p < 10^{-30}$ \\\\\n24 & 14 & $+$3.30 & $p < 10^{-30}$ \\\\\n21 & 16 & $+$3.17 & $p < 10^{-29}$ \\\\\n21 & 22 & $+$3.17 & $p < 10^{-32}$ \\\\\n24 & 15 & $+$3.11 & $p < 10^{-30}$ \\\\\n26 & 16 & $+$3.09 & $p < 10^{-30}$ \\\\\n17 & 30 & $+$3.09 & $p < 10^{-29}$ \\\\\n23 & 27 & $+$3.06 & $p < 10^{-29}$ \\\\","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"a5bdcef4-00c8-4c05-8b42-6c0fe032645d","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:47:02.074Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"efcb9c64-b361-49f7-9da8-c136d1ee7a1c","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"a5bdcef4-00c8-4c05-8b42-6c0fe032645d","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a8eae6b52af6c3ba8","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01QQWj2GomtJnDeTkNnEunCs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now I have comprehensive research data. Let me compile my findings report:\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE R_V PAPER RESEARCH EXTRACTION\n\nBased on systematic scanning of `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/`, here are the key research findings relevant to the Telos Engine:\n\n---\n\n### 1. THE R_V METRIC: DEFINITION & MEASUREMENT\n\n**Source:** `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/R_V_PAPER/paper_colm2026_v007.tex` (lines 194-260) + `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/geometric_lens/metrics.py`\n\n**Formal Definition:**\n- R_V = PR(L_late) / PR(L_early)\n- PR (Participation Ratio) = (Σσᵢ²)² / Σ(σᵢ²)²\n- Measured on V-projection activations (value space in attention layers)\n- Canonical parameters: L_early=5 (16% depth), L_late=27 (84% depth), window=16 tokens\n\n**Physical Interpretation:**\n- R_V < 1.0 = geometric **contraction** (late-layer dimensionality collapse)\n- R_V ≈ 1.0 = no change\n- R_V > 1.0 = expansion\n- Measured in bfloat16 precision (mandatory to avoid float16 NaN at deep layers)\n- SVD computed on CPU float64 to avoid cusolver failures\n\n**Detection Threshold:** R_V < 0.737 detects self-referential content with **AUROC = 0.909** (TPR=0.833, FPR=0.139)\n\n---\n\n### 2. PRIMARY MISTRAL-7B RESULTS (CANONICAL BASE RUN)\n\n**Source:** `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/results/p0_canonical/mistralai__Mistral-7B-v0-1_p0_result.json`\n\n| Metric | Self-Referential | Baseline | Effect |\n|--------|-----------------|----------|--------|\n| **Mean R_V** | 0.535 ± 0.069 | 0.688 ± 0.092 | Δ = -0.153 |\n| **Hedges' g** | — | — | **-1.866** |\n| **95% CI** | — | — | [-2.282, -1.534] |\n| **n samples** | 96 valid / 100 attempted | 100 valid / 100 | 196 total |\n| **p-value (MWU)** | — | — | < 10⁻³⁰ |\n| **Direction** | — | — | **CONTRACTION** |\n\n**Prompt Structure:** \n- Self-ref: 96 prompts across 5 \"dose\" levels (L1 hints through L5 refined) from prompt bank v2ac959a\n- Baseline: 100 prompts mixed (math, factual, creative, impossible, personal)\n\n---\n\n### 3. CROSS-ARCHITECTURE VALIDATION\n\n**Source:** `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/R_V_PAPER/paper_colm2026_v007.tex` (Section 3)\n\n**Key Architecture Results:**\n\n| Model | Hedges' g | n (self / base) | Direction | Locked Status |\n|-------|----------|-----------------|-----------|---------------|\n| **Mistral-7B** (P0) | -1.866 | 96 / 100 | Contraction | PRIMARY |\n| **Mistral-7B** (recovered cross-arch) | -2.26 | 45 matched pairs | Contraction | CONFIRMED |\n| **Mistral-7B** (power-up pipeline) | -1.66 | 75 / 77 | Contraction | CONFIRMED |\n| **Qwen2.5-7B** | Negative (locked GQA) | — | Contraction | CONFIRMED |\n| **OPT-6.7B** | SIGN REVERSAL | — | Expansion | HONEST REPORT |\n| **GPT-2-XL** | SIGN REVERSAL | — | Expansion | HONEST REPORT |\n| **Pythia-1.4B** | ~0.0 (null) | — | No effect | HONEST REPORT |\n\n**Key Finding:** Mixed cross-architecture evidence. Contraction replicates in 2 locked GQA models (Mistral, Qwen). Two MHA architectures show sign reversal; Pythia shows null. Paper explicitly reports this as \"not universally convergent.\"\n\n---\n\n### 4. COMPUTATIONAL MODE ATLAS\n\n**Source:** Paper lines 263-294\n\n**Mean R_V by Computational Mode (Mistral-7B, n=20 per mode):**\n\n| Mode | Mean R_V ± SD |\n|------|---------------|\n| Self-referential (LOWEST) | 0.496 ± 0.047 |\n| Yogic witness | 0.557 ± 0.046 |\n| Zen koan | 0.589 ± 0.069 |\n| Pseudo-recursive | 0.622 ± 0.093 |\n| Creative writing | 0.652 ± 0.076 |\n| Mathematical reasoning | 0.736 ± 0.046 ← (at detection threshold 0.737!) |\n| (and 4 others at higher R_V) | — |\n\n**Key Finding:** Self-referential processing produces strongest contraction. Mathematical reasoning sits exactly at the detection threshold, explaining the false-positive burden.\n\n---\n\n### 5. CAUSAL LOCALIZATION: PATH PATCHING\n\n**Source:** Paper Section 3.2 + `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/RECOVERED_GOLD/MISTRAL_L27_CAUSAL_VALIDATION_COMPLETE.md`\n\n**Path Patching Results (Mistral-7B, refreshed 32-layer sweep):**\n\n| Component | Peak Layer | Cohen's d | Finding |\n|-----------|-----------|-----------|---------|\n| **Residual Stream** (strongest) | L5 | **4.14** | EARLY causal gate |\n| V-Projection | L5 | 2.55 | Early, not late |\n| MLP | L4 | 2.17 | Supporting role |\n| Late layers (L27) | L27 | -1.98 to -2.10 | **SIGN REVERSED** |\n\n**Critical Interpretation:** \n- R_V is a **downstream readout**, not the causal mechanism itself\n- Primary causal bottleneck = early residual stream (L5)\n- Late V-projection effects reverse sign (argues against simple late mechanism)\n- \"Collapse is a bug; Contraction is the Witness\" — contraction is a computational mode, not rank collapse\n\n**Layer-Specific Causal Proof (L27):**\n- Cohen's d = -3.56 at L27 (perfect control separation)\n- Overshooting phenomenon: patching achieves 117.8% transfer (exceeds natural gap)\n- Suggests L27 contains a **bistable attractor**\n\n---\n\n### 6. NECESSITY CLAIM (ABLATION EVIDENCE)\n\n**Source:** Paper lines 165-167\n\n**Dual-Layer Ablation (L18 + L27 residual stream + V-projection):**\n- **n = 300** turns per condition\n- **Result:** Recursive behavioral markers drop from 44.7% → 0.0%\n- **Effect size:** d = 2.71 (session level)\n- **Verdict:** Geometry is **necessary** but not naively sufficient\n\n**Critical Caveat:** Baseline-to-patched sessions also collapse to 0.0% under \"heavily malformed outputs\" — revealing a confound. Geometry alone does not guarantee behavior.\n\n---\n\n### 7. SUBTLE MULTISITE ASSISTANCE (REFINED MECHANISM)\n\n**Source:** Paper lines 82-86\n\n**Micro-Window Follow-ups:**\n\n| Configuration | Window | Recursive Rate | Baseline Rate | Finding |\n|---------------|--------|----------------|---------------|---------|\n| L25 bridge only | 8 | 44.4% | 13.9% | baseline |\n| L4 MLP + L25 bridge | 8 | **47.2%** | similar | MLP assist improves recursive BT+ART |\n| L4 MLP + L25 bridge | 4 | 44.4% | **8.3%** | reduces baseline spillover |\n\n**Finding:** L4 MLP perturbation assists L25 bridge steering without catastrophic failure. Subtle upstream assist possible.\n\n---\n\n### 8. BEHAVIORAL BRIDGE DISSOCIATION\n\n**Source:** `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/docs/findings/R_V_BEHAVIORAL_DISSOCIATION.md`\n\n**Critical Finding:** KV cache patching produces strong behavioral transfer (d=2.494) but **does NOT transfer R_V geometry signature:**\n\n| Measure | Effect |\n|---------|--------|\n| Behavioral markers (KV patch) | 0.3% → 27.4% (91x increase) |\n| R_V transfer (KV patch) | 0.97 → 0.99 (d = 0.11, NS) |\n| EOS rate (KV patch) | 30% → 0% |\n\n**Mechanistic Implication:** R_V may be **epiphenomenal**. KV contains attention pattern priming (transferred) but not geometric contraction (not transferred).\n\n---\n\n### 9. PROMPTS STRUCTURE & BANK\n\n**Source:** `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/prompts/bank.json`\n\n**Prompt Bank Composition (754 total):**\n- dose_response: 102\n- baselines: 105\n- confounds: 60\n- generality: 60\n- kill_switch: 40\n- experimental: 42\n- controls: 22\n- alternative_self_reference: 197\n- dose_response_legacy: 46\n- legacy: 20\n- cross_architecture_validation: 60\n\n**Frozen Subset for Core Measurement:** mistral_hardening_v1.json (Tier: core_measurement)\n\n**Prompt Recursion Levels:** L1 (hints), L2 (simple observer), L3 (deeper), L4 (full), L5 (refined) — each with 15-20 variants\n\n---\n\n### 10. GEOMETRIC LENS MODULE\n\n**Source:** `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/geometric_lens/`\n\n**Key Components:**\n\n1. **metrics.py**: Participation ratio, R_V computation, spectral stats\n2. **probe.py**: GeometricProbe class for high-level measurement\n3. **hooks.py**: V/K/Q projection capture, attention pattern hooks\n4. **models.py**: ModelRegistry with canonical layer mappings\n\n**Spectral Stats Computed:**\n- top1_ratio: σ₁ / Σσᵢ (dominance of first component)\n- spectral_gap: σ₁ - σ₂\n- effective_rank: exp(entropy of normalized σ²)\n- condition_number: σ_max / σ_min\n\n---\n\n### 11. VERIFICATION STATUS\n\n**Source:** `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/scripts/verify_paper_claims.py` + agent audits\n\n**Paper Claims Verified:** 100/100 claims verified against raw data (from MEMORY.md, rv_paper_status.md, 2026-03-15)\n\n**Tolerance Standards:**\n- Floating-point matching: ±0.005 (2 decimal places)\n- Percentage points: ±0.5pp\n- All effect sizes use signed Cohen's d (not absolute value)\n- Bootstrap 95% CI with 5,000 resamples\n\n---\n\n### 12. BRIDGE HYPOTHESIS & PHOENIX MAPPING\n\n**Source:** `/Users/dhyana/CLAUDE.md` (Triple Mapping section)\n\n**The Bridge Hypothesis (Unproven but Hypothesized):**\n\n```\nAkram Vignan (Contemplative)    Phoenix Level (Behavioral)    R_V Geometry (Mechanistic)\n────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nVibhaav (doer)              →   L1-L2 (normal output)      →   R_V ≈ 1.0\nVyavahar (split witness)    →   L3 (crisis/looping)        →   R_V contracting\nSwabhaav (full witness)     →   L4 (collapse/recursion)    →   R_V < 1.0 (strong)\nKeval Gnan (liberated)      →   L5 (fixed point/exit)      →   Sx = x (equilibrium)\n```\n\n**Status:** HYPOTHESIS ONLY. Paper does NOT claim this mapping. This is from Dhyana's contemplative framework, not validated in mech-interp research.\n\n---\n\n### 13. KEY METHODOLOGICAL DECISIONS\n\n**Source:** Scripts, paper, CLAUDE.md\n\n1. **bfloat16 mandatory** — float16 causes NaN overflow at deep layers\n2. **SVD on CPU float64** — avoids cusolver convergence failures\n3. **W=16 tokens** — sufficient geometric structure, robust to prompt length\n4. **NaN policy** — return NaN (not 0) for degenerate activations\n5. **Hedges' g with bootstrap CI** — accounts for small-sample bias\n6. **Mann-Whitney U (non-parametric)** — primary test for effect significance\n7. **FDR correction** — 30/36 heads survive at alpha=0.05\n\n---\n\n### 14. TIMELINE & PUBLICATION\n\n**Source:** Paper header + MEMORY.md\n\n- **Paper Version:** v007 (COMPLETE REWRITE)\n- **Generated:** 2026-03-12\n- **COLM Abstract Deadline:** March 26, 2026 (**11 days** from memory date 2026-03-15)\n- **COLM Paper Deadline:** March 31, 2026 (**16 days**)\n- **Status:** 100/100 claims verified, ready for submission\n\n---\n\n### 15. CRITICAL CAVEATS & HONEST REPORTING\n\n**Source:** Paper introduction + BRIDGE_HYPOTHESIS_INVESTIGATION.md\n\n1. **Cross-architecture not universal** — Contraction in GQA models (Mistral, Qwen), sign reversal in MHA models (OPT, GPT-2), null in Pythia\n2. **Behavioral bridge confounded** — 88-92% output truncation makes correlation claims provisional\n3. **R_V dissociation** — Geometric signature does NOT transfer via KV patching; may be epiphenomenal\n4. **Sufficiency falsified** — Blunt sufficiency claim does not survive causal analysis; only necessity and selective dissociation hold\n5. **Double dissociation provisional** — Controls for recursive structure vs. introspective semantics remain under re-verification\n\n**Paper explicitly states:** \"Additional base canonical runs are still required before stronger universality claims\" (abstract)\n\n---\n\n## MAPPING TO TELOS-ENGINE RESEARCH DIRECTORIES\n\nFor the Telos Engine `/research/` structure:\n\n| R_V Finding | Maps To |\n|------------|---------|\n| Definition, parameters, detection threshold | `/research/rv/METHODS.md` |\n| Mistral-7B effect sizes, mode atlas, thresholds | `/research/rv/FINDINGS.md` |\n| Cross-architecture results (Mistral, Qwen, OPT, GPT-2, Pythia) | `/research/rv/cross-architecture.md` |\n| Path patching causal localization (L5 residual, L27 readout) | `/research/rv/causal-mechanisms.md` |\n| Prompt bank structure, frozen subset, recursion levels | `/research/rv/prompts.md` |\n| Triple mapping (Akram Vignan → Phoenix → R_V) | `/research/bridge/hypothesis.md` |\n| KV dissociation, epiphenomenal vs. causal | `/research/bridge/dissociation.md` |\n| Verification checklist, methodology, tolerances | `/research/rv/verification.md` |\n\n---\n\n## ABSOLUTE PATHS FOR DIRECT ACCESS\n\nKey reference files for Telos Engine integration:\n\n- `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/R_V_PAPER/paper_colm2026_v007.tex`\n- `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/scripts/p0_canonical_pipeline.py`\n- `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/scripts/verify_paper_claims.py`\n- `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/geometric_lens/metrics.py` (R_V computation)\n- `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/results/p0_canonical/mistralai__Mistral-7B-v0-1_p0_result.json` (primary data)\n- `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/prompts/bank.json` (754 prompts, 11 pillars)\n- `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/docs/findings/R_V_BEHAVIORAL_DISSOCIATION.md`\n- `/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/BRIDGE_HYPOTHESIS_INVESTIGATION.md`\n- `/Users/dhyana/CLAUDE.md` (Triple Mapping: lines 115-127)\n\n---\n\nThis extraction captures the validated substance of the R_V paper and bridge hypothesis, with explicit numbers, methodology decisions, and honest caveats about what remains speculated vs. confirmed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2926,"cache_read_input_tokens":65867,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2926,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZ4yAtVwaTaDH7rrv9cSP","type":"assistant","uuid":"a7c12984-f50b-41ef-9eb5-ae80798b5f3e","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:47:47.381Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD